summary:
The Security Council:

* Directs the Committee to review the activities of individuals who meet the criteria for designation under resolution 1857 (2008) as a matter of urgency (para 7);
* Expresses intention to consider additional targeted sanctions against the leadership of M23 and those providing external support (para 8);
* Requests the Secretary-General to report on options for redeploying MONUSCO contingents to improve its ability to implement its mandate (para 9);
* Calls on all actors to use their influence on M23 to end attacks (para 10);
* Calls on parties to allow humanitarian access and refrain from violence against civilians (para 11);
* Calls on parties to respect the civilian and humanitarian character of refugee camps and IDP sites (para 12);
* Commends MONUSCO's efforts to protect civilians and encourages continuation of efforts (para 13);
* Emphasizes that attempts to undermine MONUSCO's mandate will not be tolerated (para 14);
* Welcomes efforts of ICGLR, SADC, and AU to resolve the conflict and find a durable solution (para 15);
* Welcomes designation of Special Representative of the African Union and requests Secretary-General to report on options for high-level dialogue (para 16);
* Emphasizes the primary responsibility of the Government of DRC to reinforce State authority and governance (para 17);
* Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (para 18).
